1 Melt the butter and add the onion, garlic, ginger, chilli and curry powder, then cook very slowly for 10-15 minutes, until the onions soften completely. 2 Add the stock, cream and chutney, then bring to a simmer for 10 minutes, until the sauce starts to thicken. 3 Add the cucumber, peas, almonds and prawns, then simmer once more for two or three minutes, until the prawns are cooked, then season. 4 Serve with basmati rice and fresh coriander.